Step 1: Install G++
	sudo apt update
	sudo apt install g++

Check:
	g++ --version

Step 2: Create C++ File
	cd Desktop

	nano hello.cpp

Step 3: Write C++ Code
	Paste CODE

Step 4: Save (DO it manually)
	Ctrl + O
	Enter
	Ctrl + X

Step 5: Compile C++ Program
	g++ hello.cpp -o hello

Step 6: Run Program
	./hello
